<br>
I mean, to leave some adventure in it they need to keep it a &quot;secret&quot; until it goes live.  How fun would it be if they announced new trade skill stuff, mob retunings, and new encounters that you could practice risk free without even having to do the process of figuring it all out from point 1?<br>
<br>
Open announced testing would ruin, gimp, and trivialize an already trivial game.  VI only uses a select group of trusted testers so that this doesn't happen.  They are looking at the problem of not enough getting tested and already took a step against it.  I guess they are just sticking with this one for a little while and see if they can get it to fly.<br>
<br>
Not that I agree with VIs vision of the high end game, the leaving in of buggs they know about, pushing patches faster than they should have, etc... but I can understand their testing process.  It's not a bad one either, just short of employing 50ish testers to test all the high end stuff. <br>
<br>
And no.. I'm not part of that group of testers.<br>
<br>
